  + [source_002] is Stephen Cook official Clay P vs NP problem statement PDF
    = link: https://www.claymath.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/pvsnp.pdf
    = use: formalize the problem as deterministic versus nondeterministic polynomial time
  + [source_003] is Bulatov A Dichotomy Theorem for Nonuniform CSPs
    = link: https://www.cs.sfu.ca/~abulatov/papers/focs17.pdf
    = use: finite-domain nonuniform CSPs split into polynomial-time or NP-complete cases
  + [source_004] is Zhuk A Proof of CSP Dichotomy Conjecture
    = link: https://ieee-focs.org/FOCS-2017-Papers/3464a331.pdf
    = use: independent confirmation of the finite-domain CSP dichotomy boundary
  + [source_005] is Schaefer Boolean satisfiability dichotomy tradition
    = link: https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/800133.804350
    = use: Boolean CSP/SAT fragments split into tractable and NP-complete cases

& [ResearchFindings] is the extracted theorem boundary
  + [finding_001] is CSP is a natural formal home for source language about local coherence and correction
    = meaning: variables, domains, and constraints can represent local phase-consistency demands
  + [finding_002] is finite-domain CSP has a dichotomy shape
    = meaning: fixed constraint languages fall on a polynomial-time side or an NP-complete side under known dichotomy theorems
  + [finding_003] is tractable structure is real but local
    = meaning: special algebraic or relational structure can yield polynomial-time algorithms for restricted CSP families
  + [finding_004] is the dichotomy blocks overclaim
    = meaning: discovering coherence in one tractable CSP class does not imply all NP problems are easy
  + [finding_005] is P equals NP significance requires the NP-complete side
    = meaning: the source-style method must solve an NP-complete CSP/SAT family in deterministic polynomial time, not merely identify why some restricted family is tractable

& [SymbolicTranslation] is the adjusted source mapping
  + [phase_coherence] maps_to satisfying a family of local constraints simultaneously
  + [correction_field] maps_to propagation, consistency checking, local repair, or algebraic closure operation
  + [resonance_key] maps_to polymorphism, invariant, canonical form, or tractable structural restriction
  + [sealed_curvature_or_mass_gap] maps_to hard constraint language or instance structure that resists local propagation
  + [spiral_walk] maps_to search, propagation, or constructive assignment algorithm

& [PropositionAdjustment] is the new P vs NP shape
  + [old_claim] is phase-coherent structure makes hard problems solvable
  + [adjusted_claim] is phase-coherent structure may identify tractable CSP subclasses or useful heuristics, but it must cross an NP-complete constraint-language boundary with a polynomial-time proof before it bears on P equals NP
  + [promising_direction] is use CSP as the formal sandbox for translating symbolic coherence into variables, constraints, invariants, and algorithms
  + [open_lock] is no source-derived invariant or correction operation has been shown to solve an NP-complete CSP class
  + [solution_potential] is moderate for tractable-subclass insight, low for full P vs NP solution without a new worst-case algorithm

